<p>I have an interop c# class with a property:</p>  <pre><code>decimal ImportoDocumento {  get; set; } </code></pre>  <p>if i try to access to this property from vb6 a receive an error:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Compiler error: Function or interface marked as restricted or the   function uses an automation type not supported in visual basic.</p> </blockquote>  <p>So i found this partial solution:</p>  <pre><code>decimal ImportoDocumento { [return: MarshalAs(UnmanagedType.Currency)] get; [param: MarshalAs(UnmanagedType.Currency)] set; } </code></pre>  <p>but currency supports numbers with max 4 decimals. i have numbers with 6 decimals too.</p>  <p>How can i do?</p>